Windows- Sysadmin, reboot etc.</pre><h3 style="padding:0px;overflow-wrap:break-word;margin:1.833em 0px 0.611em;font-weight:normal;font-size:1.286em;line-height:1.222em;color:rgb(17, 17, 17);">Sed Append Example 2. Append a line after every line matching the pattern</h3><p style="margin:0px;padding:0px;overflow-wrap:break-word;margin-bottom:26px;">The below sed command will add the line “Linux Scripting” after every line that matches the pattern “Sysadmin”.</p><pre style="margin:0px;overflow-wrap:normal;overflow:auto;clear:both;padding:13px;margin-bottom:26px;font-family:Consolas, Monaco, Menlo, Courier, Verdana, sans-serif;background-color:rgb(238, 238, 238);border:1px solid rgb(221, 221, 221);font-size:13px;"><strong style="margin:0px;padding:0px;overflow-wrap:break-word;">$ sed '/Sysadmin/a \
&gt; Linux Scripting' thegeekstuff.txt</strong>

