1. Linux-Unix Sysadmin, Linux-Unix Scripting etc.
2. Databases - Oracle, mySQL etc.
3. Security (Firewall, Network, Online Security etc)
4. Storage in Linux-Unix
5. Productivity (Too many technologies to explore, not much time available)
#  Additional FAQS
6. Windows- Sysadmin, reboot etc.</pre><h3 style="padding:0px;overflow-wrap:break-word;margin:1.833em 0px 0.611em;font-weight:normal;font-size:1.286em;line-height:1.222em;color:rgb(17, 17, 17);">3. Substitute Only 2nd Occurrence of a Word Using sed s//2</h3><p style="margin:0px;padding:0px;overflow-wrap:break-word;margin-bottom:26px;">In the example below, in the output line “1. Linux Sysadmin, Linux-Unix Scripting etc.” only 2nd occurance of Linux is replaced by Linux-Unix.</p><pre style="margin:0px;overflow-wrap:normal;overflow:auto;clear:both;padding:13px;margin-bottom:26px;font-family:Consolas, Monaco, Menlo, Courier, Verdana, sans-serif;background-color:rgb(238, 238, 238);border:1px solid rgb(221, 221, 221);font-size:13px;">$ sed 's/Linux/Linux-Unix/2' thegeekstuff.txt
