uare;"><li style="margin:0px;padding:0px;overflow-wrap:break-word;">It reads the first line and places in its pattern buffer.</li><li style="margin:0px;padding:0px;overflow-wrap:break-word;">Check whether supplied command is true for this line, if true, deletes pattern space buffer and starts next cycle. i.e Read next line.</li><li style="margin:0px;padding:0px;overflow-wrap:break-word;">If supplied command doesnt true, as its normal behaviour it prints the content of the pattern space buffer.</li></ul><p style="margin:0px;padding:0px;overflow-wrap:break-word;margin-bottom:26px;">For example, 3d deletes 3rd line and prints other lines as shown below.</p><pre style="margin:0px;overflow-wrap:normal;overflow:auto;clear:both;padding:13px;margin-bottom:26px;font-family:Consolas, Monaco, Menlo, Courier, Verdana, sans-serif;background-color:rgb(238, 238, 238);border:1px solid rgb(221, 221, 221);font-size:13px;">$ sed 3d thegeekstuff.txt
